information, in this case,

00:36:15.010 --> 00:36:19.597 align:middle line:84%
because that's what we're
keying in on in these-- well,

00:36:19.597 --> 00:36:20.430 align:middle line:90%
in most of our work.

00:36:20.430 --> 00:36:22.960 align:middle line:84%
But principally in
these trauma cases,

00:36:22.960 --> 00:36:25.950 align:middle line:84%
we're working at very
low EEG frequencies.

00:36:25.950 --> 00:36:28.690 align:middle line:84%
And so the information, very
slowly, but the brain still

00:36:28.690 --> 00:36:29.860 align:middle line:90%
gets it.

00:36:29.860 --> 00:36:35.260 align:middle line:84%
And so the outline here
reflects that EEG amplitude.

00:36:35.260 --> 00:36:39.250 align:middle line:84%
This signal here is
actually the raw signal

00:36:39.250 --> 00:36:42.020 align:middle line:90%
