00:37:15.410 --> 00:37:17.480 align:middle line:84%
But actually, at this
very low frequency,

00:37:17.480 --> 00:37:21.350 align:middle line:84%
it's almost like watching
the swells of the ocean.

00:37:21.350 --> 00:37:24.450 align:middle line:84%
It's just the signal moves
up and down very slowly.

00:37:24.450 --> 00:37:28.570 align:middle line:84%
And here, the brain
cares about that signal

00:37:28.570 --> 00:37:31.270 align:middle line:84%
because that signal
is so important

00:37:31.270 --> 00:37:33.070 align:middle line:90%
to its own organization.

00:37:33.070 --> 00:37:34.740 align:middle line:84%
That's why it
matters to the brain.

00:37:34.740 --> 00:37:38.470 align:middle line:84%
And that's why it's so acutely
interested, even though we

00:37:38.470 --> 00:37:41.270 align:middle line:84%
as observers say
it's so slow, how

00:37:41.270 --> 00:37:43.140 align:middle line:84%
can the brain get
anything out of that?

00:37:43.140 --> 00:37:48.006 align:middle line:84%
But it does because it's
the brain's own dance,

00:37:48.006 --> 00:37:49.630 align:middle line:84%
and that's why the
brain is interested.

00:37:49.630 --> 00:37:52.510 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So is the signal coming
